 Are there any guilds that take care of most things in game?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iulianefv>iulianeFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wilderness Girl</span><br>  Posts: 208<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/13/02 6:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/leebradleyadams/EQ000014.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: looking around</span><hr size=1> To be honest, your best option is talk to the people you group with and like. Maybe one of them is in a guild you might like? Good luck <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=210273" target="_blank"><img src="http://leagueofhonour.com/Iulisig.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=umar666>Umar666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/15/02 11:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=354.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: looking around</span><hr size=1> Honestly, I believe the process of hunting up a guild is even more important here than on other servers, but then again, I have always hated guild-hoppers.<br>
<br>
Heck, I have even gotten a few tells recently asking why someone of my level is still unguilded.  The answer is simple.  I am being careful who I associate with long-term (i.e., guild with).  This includes checking several times a day to see if the guild is even playing together with its current members.  :-)  That kind of stuff is important to me.  It is also important to me that people realize the game is simply a game (a focus which I lost for a while on my original server oh so long ago).  Uber is NOT the pixels you wear... it is the skill of the player, of the group you are with, and the team you are part of.<br>
<br>
It is also useful to check how involved the guild leader is.  I have fairly defined views on leadership, but I prob have a different background than most.<br>
<br>
Don't just &quot;join&quot; a guild to see if it is what you want.  Investigate it.  I have finally formally applied to one guild in particular.  Unfortunately, the investigative process DOES take time, but if you want a good guild experience, the time is well worth investing.<br>
<br>
But yes, it would be nice to have stuff in one place.  But some guilds with message boards have only a few online at a time, and have only 3 people posting to the boards a week.  Not what I want in a guild, but that may work for others.<br>
<br>
Marquis, 46th Mage<br>
