<br>
I've been thinking of looking for a guild myself though I have decided that it is not at the uppermost top of my list of things to do.<br>
<br>
Excluding what the guild is about I look for these things:<br>
<br>
The seasons of players on at the times I play.  This is good for grouping and such.  No use in joining a guild with members to low or to high if your going to be soloing and not join in the fun of certain guild events. <br>
<br>
The website/message board (if they have one) and see what activity is there. Don't really see the point in having one if it's not used.  I'm a former member of Tinker's Pride.  We were required (at least at one point) to post something once a week.  This was good because we knew on a constant basis who was still around and could keep each other up to speed on what was going on event's wise and such.  It also brought us closer as friends as some (like me) played at odd hours.<br>
<br>
Best of luck to ya!<br>
<br>
Hoch<br>
